      In the **City of the Bridgeless Chasm**, where the only path across the abyss was a rope bridge woven from the hair of the dead, there stood a **weighmaster** named **Kael**. His duty was to judge the worth of travelers before they crossed, using the **Scale of the Unseen**—a balance with one pan of gold and the other of shadow. The law was clear: *‘No soul may pass unless the scale finds them true.’* Those whose gold pan **outweighed** the shadow were granted passage. Those whose shadow **drowned the light** were cast into the chasm, their names forgotten.

